# EduPredict Project Rules

## Project Context

**Purpose:** Predictive tool for universities to decide "Should we add an AI program?"
**Deadline:** March 9, 2026 (Professor deliverable)
**Architecture:** LangChain + Chroma + HuggingFace (local, free)
**Database:** SQLite

## File Locations

- Frontend: `~/Desktop/Edu/index-2.html` (source), `~/edupredict/index-2.html` (deployed)
- Backend: `~/edupredict/src/`
- Data: `~/edupredict/data/`
- Models: `~/edupredict/models/`
- Repo: https://github.com/GaneshMunagala714/Edupredict-

## Architecture

### RAG Stack
- **Framework:** LangChain
- **Vector DB:** Chroma (local, no API keys)
- **Embeddings:** HuggingFace (free, local)
- **LLM:** HuggingFace (Llama 2 or Mistral)
- **Backend:** FastAPI
- **Database:** SQLite

### Data Pipeline (Tier 1 - Auto-fetch)
```
Scheduler (weekly) → Fetcher → Compare → Clean → Append → Retrain
```

## Project Structure

```
edupredict/
├── .cursor/rules/
│   └── edupredict-rag.mdc (this file)
├── data/
│   ├── raw/              # Downloaded datasets
│   ├── processed/        # Cleaned, standardized
│   └── metadata.json     # Track last fetch, checksums
├── src/
│   ├── fetcher.py        # Check APIs, download new data
│   ├── cleaner.py        # Standardize formats
│   ├── scheduler.py      # Weekly job runner
│   ├── retrain.py        # Retrain model trigger
│   ├── rag/
